column1: #Text=Early yesterday afternoon local time , a 7.5 magnitude earthquake hit Afghanistan , Pakistan and North India , with its epicenter in the Hindu Kush mountain range which stretches from Afghanistan to North Pakistan , causing damage to life and buildings .
#Text=A Wikinews correspondent felt the shock waves in Behror , Rajasthan at 2:50 PM IST ( 0920 UTC ) .
#Text=Hundreds of people died in this disaster .
#Text=The death toll is highest in Pakistan .
#Text=Pakistani officials yesterday afternoon declared over 145 people were found dead .
#Text=United States Geological Survey reported the earthquake occurred at 212 km depth due to reverse faulting .
#Text=Twelve students died in the rush due to trembles , in an Afghani girls ' school in Takhar , near Badakhshan .
#Text=Two elderly women in Kashmir died due to heart attack .
#Text=Some people in Pakistan died by crushing by roof collapse .
#Text=The Map of the disaster Image : USGS .
#Text=Indian states Punjab , Jammu and Kashmir , Rajasthan , Uttar Pradesh and Delhi National Capital Region were affected .
#Text=Srinagar experienced a power cutoff after the earthquake .
#Text=During yesterday afternoon , Indian Prime minister Narendra Modi communicated with Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif , volunteering help .
#Text=He also tweeted " Heard about strong earthquake in Afghanistan-Pakistan region whose tremors have been felt in parts of India .
